CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1953, pg. 36, reads: "The JWJ's Open House - Last Sunday, Oct. 11, found Pittsburghers wending their way to the open house - house warming given by the John Wesley Johnsons in their new home at 3510 Iowa Street. Pittsburghers all were invited through Toki's column...  Right photo, some of the smartly frocked guests who attended the affair. - Teenie Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Women, including Ruby Young Buchanan wearing dark velvet near right, standing in front of fireplace in Johnson home, 3510 Iowa Street, Upper Hill District
